p4
VOlakkudi G.R. Pravin rendered a vocal concert at the 70 {+t} {+h} monthly music festival of the Tiruchi Tamil Isai Sangam at its premises in the city recently. Pravin, grandson of noted vocalist P.V. Ganesa Iyer, commenced his concert with a Lalgudi varnam in Charukesi ragam.DKP's compositionThe highlight of the concert was the rendering of &#8216;Gajamukha Jananathan' composed by D.K. Pattammal in Lathangi ragam. This was followed by the song &#8216;Kandanaalmudhal' composed by N.S. Chidambaram in Madhuvanti ragam. Pravin concluded the programme, with a thillana of Lalgudi Jayaraman in Revathi ragam. He was ably accompanied by Sherthalai M.N. Sathiyamoorthy on the violin, Tiruchi R. Thayumanavan on the mridangam and Tiruchi Moorthy on the ganjira.L.N. Lakshmanan, president of the Tamil Isai Sangam, presided over the concert. A. Kaliamoorthy, former Superintendent of Police, who was the chief guest, explained how Tamizh is being acclaimed world over. He said people who accord importance to their mother tongue always have achieved great laurels. He further added Sangam literary works have shown the right path to the people andquoted various Tamil poems to drive home the point that people should develop confidence to successfully face the future challenges. K. Rangarajan, secretary, Tamil Isai Sangam, N. Mohan, vice president, and others offered felicitations.
